  <title>How to manage Containers?</title>

  <p><gui>KOOMPI OS Control Center</gui> allows you to manage various <gui>pix</gui> containers from multiple sources seamlessly in a unified place.</p>
  
  <p>It allows us to initialize or enter containers through the <gui>Containers</gui> menu.</p>
  
<media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/koompi-control-center-subsystem.png"/>

  <p> You can initialize the <gui>pix</gui> container by:</p>
  
 <list>
        <item><p>Clicking on the <gui>+</gui> button in the desired container.</p></item>
        <item><p>Upon clicking, a Read-only window opens, and the container gets created.</p></item>
        <item><p>Now, the <gui>+</gui> icon would have changed to a terminal icon which means the container's creation is successful.</p></item>
 </list>
 
 <media type="image" its:translate="no" src="media/koompi-control-center-subsystem-enter.png"/>
 
 <p> You can enter the <gui>pix</gui> container by clicking on the terminal icon, which opens a terminal window logged into the <gui>pix_managed</gui> container.</p>
